      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
          <updateDate>2016-09-14T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Classified Information Protection Act of 2016</b></p> <p>This bill amends the federal criminal code to specify that the government need not prove intent to harm the United States when prosecuting a: (1) person entrusted with national defense information who permits the loss or removal of such information through gross negligence; or (2) government employee, contractor, or consultant who commits unauthorized removal and retention of classified material.</p>]]></text>
